SUMMARY
NCCIC/ICS-CERT is aware of a public report of a hardcoded password vulnerability affecting Daktronics Vanguard highway notification sign configuration software. According to this report, the vulnerability is a hardcoded password that could allow unauthorized access to the highway sign. This report was reported to ICS-CERT by the Federal Highway Administration. ICS-CERT has notified the affected vendor of the report and has asked the vendor to confirm the vulnerability and identify mitigations. ICS-CERT is issuing this alert to provide early notice of the report and identify baseline mitigations for reducing risks to these and other cybersecurity attacks.
Proof of Concept is known to be publicly available. ICS-CERT recommends entities review sign messaging, update access credentials, and harden communication paths to the signs.



